<topic id="author-xhtml-extensions" >
  <title>XHTML Author Actions</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>XHTML Document Type<indexterm>Author extensions</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>A variety of actions are available in the XHTML framework that can be added to the
        <uicontrol>XHTML</uicontrol> menu, the <uicontrol>Author custom actions</uicontrol> toolbar,
      the contextual menu, and the <uicontrol>Content Completion Assistant</uicontrol>. The
      following default actions are included in the toolbar and the <uicontrol>XHTML</uicontrol>
      menu and are readily available when editing in <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode (most of
      them are also available, by default, in the contextual menu):</p>
    <p>
      <dl>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_bold.png" placement="inline" id="image_tyc_rr2_fr"
              />Bold</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Changes the style of the selected text to <codeph>bold</codeph> by surrounding it with
              <codeph>b</codeph> tag. You can use this action on multiple non-contiguous
            selections.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_italic.png" placement="inline" id="image_uyc_rr2_fr"
              />Italic</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Changes the style of the selected text to <codeph>italic</codeph> by surrounding it
            with <codeph>i</codeph> tag. You can use this action on multiple non-contiguous
            selections.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_underline.png" placement="inline"
                id="image_izc_rr2_fr"/>Underline</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Changes the style of the selected text to <codeph>underline</codeph> by surrounding it
            with <codeph>u</codeph> tag. You can use this action on multiple non-contiguous
            selections.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Link20.png" id="image_olk_fdm_kr"/>Insert a hypertext
              link</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Inserts an <codeph>a</codeph> element with an <codeph>href</codeph> attribute at the
            caret position. You can type the URL of the reference you want to insert or use the
                <uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_browse_list.png" id="image_plq_htz_jr"
              />Browse</uicontrol> drop-down list to select it using one of the following
              options:<ul id="ul_pqr_4tz_jr">
              <li><uicontrol>Browse for local file:</uicontrol> Opens the <wintitle>Open</wintitle>
                dialog to select a local file.</li>
              <li><uicontrol>Browse for remote file:</uicontrol> Opens the <wintitle>Open
                  URL</wintitle> dialog to select a remote file.</li>
              <li><uicontrol>Browse for archived file:</uicontrol> Opens the <wintitle>Archive
                  Browser</wintitle> to select a file from an archive.</li>
              <li><uicontrol>Browse Data Source Explorer:</uicontrol> Open the <wintitle>Data Source
                  Explorer</wintitle> to select a file from a connected data source.</li>
              <li><uicontrol>Search for file:</uicontrol> Opens the <wintitle>Find
                  Resource</wintitle> dialog to search for a file.</li>
            </ul></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_insert_graphic.png" placement="inline"
                id="image_kzc_rr2_fr"/>Insert image reference</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Inserts a graphic object at the caret position. This is done by inserting an
              <codeph>img</codeph> element regardless of the current context. The following
            graphical formats are supported: GIF, JPG, JPEG, BMP, PNG, SVG.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry>
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_headings.png" placement="inline"
                id="image_jzc_rr2_fr"/>Headings</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>A drop-down list that includes actions for inserting <codeph>h1</codeph>,
              <codeph>h2</codeph>, <codeph>h3</codeph>, <codeph>h4</codeph>, <codeph>h5</codeph>,
              <codeph>h6</codeph> elements.</dd>
        </dlentry>
